certain site, a certain chair.

00:44:33.660 --> 00:44:38.330
So the chairs are the lattice sites
and the people are the liquid in

00:44:38.330 --> 00:44:42.990
motion. What is going to enhance
the ability to get to the lattice

00:44:42.990 --> 00:44:47.660
site? In other words,
to crystallize? Mobility is an

00:44:47.660 --> 00:44:52.750
issue.
Mobility of atoms in the liquid is

00:44:52.750 --> 00:44:58.250
going to enhance the ability to
crystallize. What is another factor?

00:44:58.250 --> 00:45:03.750
Well, the arrangement of the chairs.
If the chairs are simply arranged,

00:45:03.750 --> 00:45:09.250
it is easy to get to them. If the
chairs have complexity in their

00:45:09.250 --> 00:45:14.750
arrangement then it is more
difficult. Let's liken that to the

00:45:14.750 --> 00:45:20.250
complexity of the crystal lattice,
complexity of the solid crystal

00:45:20.250 --> 00:45:38.366
structure.
Systems that have complex crystal

00:45:05.000 --> 00:45:09.000
structures are more apt to form
glasses than systems that have

00:45:09.000 --> 00:45:13.000
simple crystal structures.
